<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-409-850  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 409 850.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  April 30 1990 v7 n18 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>3Com changes marketing direction under Benhamou. (Eric Benhamou)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>3Com Corp has elected Eric Benhamou president and chief operatingofficer.andP;  Most recently, Benhamou was executive vice-president ofproduct operations on 3Com's Executive Committee.andP;  Benhamou willhave sole responsibility for day-to-day operations as 3Com, givinghim the opportunity to put into effect his redesign of thecompany's marketing strategy.andP;  Previously, 3Com promoted computerequipment, such as workstations and servers, but Benhamou's planfocuses on integrating its core network equipment such asinternetwork bridges and routers, adapters and software, atcustomer sites, regardless of the computing equipment used there.andO;3Com is showing signs of a financial comeback, and needs focusedleadership to keep abreast of competition.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   3Com Corp. (officials and employees).andO;Ticker:    COMS.andO;Topic:     ExecutivePromotion of EmployeeChief Operating OfficersMarketing StrategyLocal Area NetworksCommunications Equipment.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Eric Benhamou. (portrait)Person:    Benhamou, Eric (selection and appointment).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>